metadata.initialMessage: Hey! I'm curious about your thoughts on AI in 2026. What do you think are the most exciting developments we'll see?
metadata.finalTopicGoal: Learn about their company, what they're working on, or their current projects

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Hey! I'm curious about your thoughts on AI in 2026. What do you think are the most exciting developments we'll see?

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: Yeah, it's gonna be wild when agents just handle all those annoying clicks across our apps for us, right?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Yeah, I'm really hyped for agents that actually finish real tasks across apps instead of just chatting, it's gonna be such a vibe!

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: deep into building some agentic loops for dev tasks, but have you checked out any of those new frameworks yet?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Totally, but I'm actually curious if you're hacking on any agent projects right now or just keeping an eye on things?

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: Oh nice, PydanticAI is super clean, but do you think we'll even be manually coding these agent loops by next year?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Yeah, I've been messing with PydanticAI lately and it's actually super clean for building those complex loops you're into!

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: I'm sticking with dev for now but honestly I'm getting pretty curious about how agents will start messing with robotics and hardware too, right?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Yeah, I'm thinking it'll be mostly natural language steering by then, but are you planning to stay in the dev space or try something new?

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: Honestly, I think we're heading toward a future where every device has its own little brain that just works in the background, you know?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Yeah, seeing agents move things in the real world is gonna be sick, but honestly I'm just waiting for a bot that can fold my laundry!

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: Yeah, I bet cloud stays for the huge tasks, but are you trying to move all your own stuff onto local hardware already?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Totally, but I'm curious if you think we'll still need big cloud models once everything has its own local brain?

conversation.speaker: User (Receiver)
conversation.message: Haha, that's such a sick start, but do you ever miss training those models from scratch or do you prefer this new era?

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: I'm testing local setups now, and I actually got into AI just by messing around with neural nets in school because they're honestly so cool!

conversation.speaker: Khagendra (Sender)
conversation.message: Honestly, I don't miss the headache of training from scratch since we can ship such wild stuff so fast now and actually see it work!
